B5 - Attend 2 cybersecurity related talks/seminars

Objective
The goal of this activity was to gain additional knowledge about cybersecurity concepts by attending seminars and understanding real-world security practices.

Method
I attended 1 online and one in person cybersecurity seminars. Both sessions focused on explaining  cyber threats, security risks, and methods used to protect systems and user in real-world environments.

Seminar 1 - Key poinst learned
- Cyberattacks often target users through phishing and social engineering
- Weak passwords and lack of security awareness increase in risk
- Attackers commonly exploit human behaviour rahter than technical flaws
- Basic protections such as strong passwords and awareness are essential

Seminar 2 - Key points learned
- Importance of multi-layered security approaches
- Role of cybersecurity professionals in protecting systems
- Common threats such as malware, data breaches, and unauthorised access
- Need for continous monitoring and security updates

Outcome
These seminars improved my understanding of how cybersecurity concepts are applied in real-world scenarios. They reinforced the importance of both technical security measures and user awareness in preventing cyberattacks.

Reflection
This activity showed that cybersecurity is not only about technology but also about humanh behaviour. Many attacks succeed due to user mistakes, highlighting the importance of education and awareness. It reinforced concepts leanred in this unit, such as phishing, authentication, and system security.
